#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:62
msgid "Constructing Messages"
msgstr "Construire des messages."

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:64
msgid ""
"In Flower, the server and clients communicate by sending and receiving "
"|message_link|_ objects. A ``Message`` carries a ``RecordDict`` as its "
"main payload. The ``RecordDict`` is like a Python dictionary that can "
"contain multiple records of different types. There are three main types "
"of records:"
msgstr ""
"Dans Flower, le serveur et les clients communiquent en envoyant et "
"recevant des objets |message_link|_. Un ``Message`` transporte un "
"``RecordDict`` comme principal payload. Le ``RecordDict`` est comme un "
"dictionnaire Python qui peut contenir plusieurs enregistrements de types "
"différents. Il existe trois principaux types d'enregistrements :"

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:69
msgid ""
"|arrayrecord_link|_: Contains model parameters as a dictionary of NumPy "
"arrays"
msgstr ""
"|arrayrecord_link|_: Contient des paramètres de modèle sous forme de "
"dictionnaire de tableaux NumPy"

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:70
msgid ""
"|metricrecord_link|_: Contains training or evaluation metrics as a "
"dictionary of integers, floats, lists of integers, or lists of floats."
msgstr ""
"|metricrecord_link|_: Contient des métriques d'entraînement ou "
"d'évaluation sous forme de dictionnaire d'integers, de flottants, de "
"listes d'integers ou de listes de flottants."

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:72
msgid ""
"|configrecord_link|_: Contains configuration parameters as a dictionary "
"of integers, floats, strings, booleans, or bytes. Lists of these types "
"are also supported."
msgstr ""
"|configrecord_link|_: Contient des paramètres de configuration sous forme"
" de dictionnaire d'integers, de flottants, de chaînes, de booléens ou de "
"bytes. Les listes de ces types sont également supportées."

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:75
msgid ""
"Let's see a few examples of how to work with these types of records and, "
"ultimately, construct a ``RecordDict`` that can be sent over a "
"``Message``."
msgstr ""
"Voyons quelques exemples de comment travailler avec ces types de "
"registres et, finalement, construire un ``RecordDict`` qui peut être "
"envoyé sur un ``Message``."

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:102
msgid "Revisiting replying from ClientApps"
msgstr "Revisiter la réponse des applications Client"

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-customize-the-client-pytorch.rst:104
