msgid "Run the App Locally"
msgstr "Exécutez l'App Localement"

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-write-your-first-flower-app-pytorch.rst:187
msgid ""
"Running on SuperGrid is the recommended way to run collaborative AI "
"workflows with Flower. However, it is also useful to run the same app "
"locally while you are developing or debugging."
msgstr ""
"L'exécution sur SuperGrid est la méthode recommandée pour exécuter des "
"workflows d'intelligence artificielle collaborative avec Flower. "
"Cependant, il est également utile d'exécuter la même application "
"localement pendant que vous développez ou déboguez."

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-write-your-first-flower-app-pytorch.rst:191
msgid ""
"From the ``quickstart-pytorch`` directory, install the app and its "
"dependencies into your Python environment:"
msgstr ""
"À partir du répertoire ``quickstart-pytorch``, installez l'application et"
" ses dépendances dans votre environnement Python :"

#: ../../source/tutorial-series-write-your-first-flower-app-pytorch.rst:199
msgid ""
"Then run the app locally with the command below. Flower will start a "
"managed local SuperLink -- a distilled version of SuperGrid -- and "
"execute the app with simulated SuperNodes on your machine. The first run "
"can take longer because the app needs to download CIFAR-10. With the flag"
